Class BankAccount

  • com.stripe.android.model.BankAccount
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StripeParamsModel

    public class BankAccount
implements StripeParamsModel

    Model class representing a bank account that can be used to create a token via the protocol outlined in [the Stripe

    • documentation.](https://stripe.com/docs/api/java#create_bank_account_token)

        Model class representing a bank account that can be used to create a token via the protocol outlined in [the Stripe

        • documentation.](https://stripe.com/docs/api/java#create_bank_account_token)

      • BankAccount

        public BankAccount(java.lang.String accountNumber,
                   java.lang.String countryCode,
                   java.lang.String currency,
                   java.lang.String routingNumber)

        Constructor used to create a BankAccount object with the required parameters to send to Stripe's server.

        Parameters:
        accountNumber - the account number for this BankAccount
        countryCode - the two-letter country code that this account was created in
        currency - the currency of this account
        routingNumber - the routing number of this account. Can be null for non US bank accounts.

      • BankAccount

        public BankAccount(java.lang.String accountHolderName,
                   java.lang.String accountHolderType,
                   java.lang.String bankName,
                   java.lang.String countryCode,
                   java.lang.String currency,
                   java.lang.String fingerprint,
                   java.lang.String last4,
                   java.lang.String routingNumber)

        Constructor with no account number used internally to initialize an object from JSON returned from the server.

        Parameters:
        accountHolderName - the account holder's name
        accountHolderType - the interface BankAccount.BankAccountType
        bankName - the name of the bank
        countryCode - the two-letter country code of the country in which the account was opened
        currency - the three-letter currency code
        fingerprint - the account fingerprint
        last4 - the last four digits of the account number
        routingNumber - the routing number of the bank
